WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.170 --> 00:00:04.410
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:00:46.672 --> 00:00:49.130
MAN:
All right!

3
00:00:49.341 --> 00:00:51.457
Give it up for Smash Mouth!

4
00:00:51.635 --> 00:00:54.798
Let's hear it. come on!

5
00:00:56.181 --> 00:01:01.051
Hangin' Chad. coming back live
at the KQSF Annual Beach Bash.

6
00:01:01.228 --> 00:01:04.186
Winding it up with
our special guest.

7
00:01:04.356 --> 00:01:09.522
the stunningly beautiful.
Phoebe Halliwell

8
00:01:09.695 --> 00:01:11.527
of "Ask Phoebe" fame.

9
00:01:11.697 --> 00:01:13.529
Okay. so. what's your deal?

10
00:01:13.699 --> 00:01:15.406
Are you psychic. is that it?

11
00:01:15.576 --> 00:01:18.534
-I'm sorry?
-I mean you gotta be. don't you?

12
00:01:18.704 --> 00:01:20.615
Your column has skyrocketed.

13
00:01:20.831 --> 00:01:25.450
all the critics rave about how
amazingly insightful your advice is.

14
00:01:25.627 --> 00:01:26.833
How else do you explain it?

15
00:01:27.045 --> 00:01:29.503
I just think I read people really well.

16
00:01:29.715 --> 00:01:31.672
Oh. you do. do you?

17
00:01:31.842 --> 00:01:32.877
Can you read me?

18
00:01:36.388 --> 00:01:38.595
I don't know.
Write a letter and we'll see.

19
00:01:38.807 --> 00:01:40.263
Come on. give it a shot.

20
00:01:40.475 --> 00:01:43.968
You guys wanna see her do it.
don't you?

21
00:01:44.187 --> 00:01:45.598
[CHEERING]

22
00:01:45.814 --> 00:01:48.602
All right. all right.

23
00:01:49.192 --> 00:01:51.024
What do you want advice on?

24
00:01:51.194 --> 00:01:52.684
Okay. let's see.

25
00:01:52.904 --> 00:01:56.522
There's this woman that I like.
and I'd like to ask her out.

26
00:01:56.742 --> 00:02:00.235
But I'm afraid she'll say no.
What should I do?

27
00:02:05.125 --> 00:02:08.038
Well. why don't you just ask me
and find out?

28
00:02:35.113 --> 00:02:36.444
Hey. are you out of your mind?

29
00:02:36.615 --> 00:02:37.730
What are you doing here?

30
00:02:37.949 --> 00:02:39.405
Freyja sent me.

31
00:02:39.576 --> 00:02:41.362
She wants to know
what's taking so long.

32
00:02:41.578 --> 00:02:43.239
Freyja?

33
00:02:43.413 --> 00:02:45.529
For a mythical character.
she sure does worry a lot.

34
00:02:45.749 --> 00:02:47.410
She's not the only one
who's worried.

35
00:02:48.627 --> 00:02:49.867
He's an Elder. Chris.

36
00:02:50.045 --> 00:02:52.127
How much longer do you really
expect us to keep him?

37
00:02:52.339 --> 00:02:53.704
Don't tell me he's complaining.

38
00:02:53.924 --> 00:02:55.164
Yes. a lot actually.

39
00:02:55.384 --> 00:02:57.250
I don't believe it!
Banish the guy to an island

40
00:02:57.427 --> 00:03:00.465
filled with beautiful women
and he still complains.

41
00:03:00.639 --> 00:03:02.380
-I can't win.
-How much longer?

42
00:03:02.599 --> 00:03:03.680
Until I'm ready.

43
00:03:05.185 --> 00:03:07.677
I'm sorry. but I haven't finished
what I came here to do yet.

44
00:03:07.854 --> 00:03:09.811
And I need Leo
out of the way until I can.

45
00:03:10.565 --> 00:03:13.478
More importantly. the sisters
can't find him before I'm ready.

46
00:03:13.652 --> 00:03:14.938
-Or else...
-I know.

47
00:03:16.822 --> 00:03:18.608
We all understand the risks.

48
00:03:19.366 --> 00:03:22.324
I'd never hurt you. Mist.

49
00:03:22.869 --> 00:03:26.328
-You know that.
-You would if you had to.

50
00:03:26.665 --> 00:03:28.997
I know that too.

51
00:03:30.293 --> 00:03:31.624
PIPER:
<i>Chris. are you up there?</i>

52
00:03:33.130 --> 00:03:34.620
You better go.

53
00:03:47.811 --> 00:03:51.270
Please. Hurry.

54
00:03:57.487 --> 00:04:00.696
-Hey. do you have any laundry?
-Uh...

55
00:04:01.908 --> 00:04:04.650
No. no. I'm good. thanks.

56
00:04:05.579 --> 00:04:08.287
I'm gonna get your sisters.
We have another demon to vanquish.

57
00:04:08.498 --> 00:04:10.034
Okey-dokey.

58
00:04:16.506 --> 00:04:19.544
Hi. I'm sorry if I embarrassed
you back there.

59
00:04:19.760 --> 00:04:22.752
-I'm glad it was on the radio.
-I don't know why I answered like that.

60
00:04:22.929 --> 00:04:24.966
-It was...
-It was dead on. that's what it was.

61
00:04:25.182 --> 00:04:28.345
It was exactly what I was feeling.
Nervous about asking you out.

62
00:04:29.019 --> 00:04:30.680
Really? You were?

63
00:04:31.813 --> 00:04:34.646
Well. then maybe I should ask you out
and just take the pressure off.

64
00:04:38.528 --> 00:04:40.519
I just don't know
what's the matter with me.

65
00:04:41.448 --> 00:04:43.064
It's gotta be the heat or something.

66
00:04:45.786 --> 00:04:49.245
-Bayview Café. say. 1:00?
-I'll be there.

67
00:04:49.414 --> 00:04:50.745
CHRIS:
Phoebe.

68
00:04:50.916 --> 00:04:53.203
Chris. what are you doing here?

69
00:04:53.376 --> 00:04:55.492
Listen. I gotta get back.

70
00:04:55.670 --> 00:04:57.832
-Don't be late.
-I won't be.

71
00:05:02.469 --> 00:05:04.585
Trok demon. Remember?

72
00:05:04.930 --> 00:05:08.594
-Oh. Chris. get a life.
-Come on.

73
00:05:08.767 --> 00:05:11.475
Stop! Stop!

74
00:05:11.686 --> 00:05:12.972
Please?

75
00:05:13.146 --> 00:05:14.557
[DOGS BARKING]

76
00:05:14.731 --> 00:05:17.098
Sit! Heel!

77
00:05:20.821 --> 00:05:22.403
Stop!

78
00:05:25.158 --> 00:05:27.946
I gotta get a real job.

79
00:05:30.705 --> 00:05:31.991
Oh.

80
00:05:33.375 --> 00:05:34.865
Trok demon?

81
00:05:35.085 --> 00:05:36.826
What now?
Can't you see I'm working?

82
00:05:48.974 --> 00:05:52.592
All right. can we get this started
because I have to go...

83
00:05:52.811 --> 00:05:54.142
Where did they come from?

84
00:05:54.354 --> 00:05:56.095
He wouldn't let me
take them back first.

85
00:05:56.314 --> 00:05:58.772
-Back?
-Yeah. I'm a...

86
00:05:58.942 --> 00:06:00.182
...dog walker.

87
00:06:00.360 --> 00:06:01.691
The temp agency messed up.

88
00:06:01.862 --> 00:06:03.193
[PHOEBE SNICKERS]

89
00:06:03.989 --> 00:06:07.402
Do you mind? We have to summon
the demon while he's still on our plane.

90
00:06:07.576 --> 00:06:10.443
-Piper!
-Oh. Chris. lighten up.

91
00:06:10.620 --> 00:06:13.954
Sending us after all these demons
is getting to be a real drag.

92
00:06:14.124 --> 00:06:17.333
-Yeah. you're working us like dogs.
-I don't see Piper complaining.

93
00:06:17.502 --> 00:06:20.460
No. because Piper doesn't complain
about anything anymore.

94
00:06:20.630 --> 00:06:22.166
Ever since Leo left
to become an Elder.

95
00:06:22.340 --> 00:06:25.583
all she does is walk
around the house all chipper.

96
00:06:25.802 --> 00:06:27.713
- So?
PAIGE: So it's unusual.

97
00:06:27.929 --> 00:06:29.590
What's worse. it's not Piper.

98
00:06:29.806 --> 00:06:31.206
PIPER:
I'd love to have a play date.

99
00:06:31.349 --> 00:06:34.011
Maybe we can call Jennie
and she can bring baby Josie.

100
00:06:34.185 --> 00:06:37.394
And then I'll bring the juice
and maybe bake some muffins. and...

101
00:06:37.564 --> 00:06:40.147
Oh. how cute.

102
00:06:40.734 --> 00:06:41.769
PIPER:
Okay?

103
00:06:41.943 --> 00:06:43.775
-She's getting worse.
-Definitely.

104
00:06:43.987 --> 00:06:46.194
-Do you have a spell?
-Right out of the <i>Book.</i>

105
00:06:46.406 --> 00:06:48.989
After you summon him.
make sure Piper freezes him.

106
00:06:49.159 --> 00:06:50.866
Otherwise you'll never
get the spell off.

107
00:06:51.077 --> 00:06:53.193
Take these guys to the attic.
they'll be fine there.

108
00:06:53.371 --> 00:06:55.988
- Wait. Me? Whoa.
PAIGE: Yeah. you. Go.

109
00:06:56.458 --> 00:06:57.493
[DOGS BARKING]

110
00:06:59.210 --> 00:07:02.293
-Alrighty. are we ready?
-Alrighty.

111
00:07:02.464 --> 00:07:06.549
Phoebe. have I told you how much
I love your new 'do. it's fabulous!

112
00:07:06.718 --> 00:07:09.335
-Very chipper.
-Okay. let's do this.

113
00:07:09.512 --> 00:07:11.378
You take this.

114
00:07:22.150 --> 00:07:23.231
[DEMON GROWLS]

115
00:07:23.401 --> 00:07:24.812
Piper. freeze him!

116
00:07:25.028 --> 00:07:26.063
[PHOEBE SCREAMS]

117
00:07:27.405 --> 00:07:29.146
[LAUGHING]

118
00:07:29.366 --> 00:07:30.606
What did you do that for?

119
00:07:30.825 --> 00:07:32.816
I don't know. I didn't mean to.

120
00:07:33.328 --> 00:07:34.659
[ROARING]

121
00:07:34.829 --> 00:07:36.536
[GRUNTING]

122
00:07:38.583 --> 00:07:40.290
<i>"From other worlds far and near</i>

123
00:07:40.460 --> 00:07:42.497
<i>Let's get him the Trok out of here"</i>

124
00:07:43.630 --> 00:07:44.665
[YELLING]

125
00:07:50.261 --> 00:07:51.672
Everybody okay?

126
00:07:51.888 --> 00:07:53.754
Yeah. That was awesome.

127
00:08:53.742 --> 00:08:56.985
What kind of whitelighter can't heal?

128
00:08:57.162 --> 00:09:00.200
-For the record. you can't heal either.
-I'm half whitelighter.

129
00:09:00.373 --> 00:09:02.614
How come you didn't tell us this
before we hired you?

130
00:09:02.792 --> 00:09:06.001
Because you didn't hire me.
I was assigned by the Elders.

131
00:09:06.171 --> 00:09:08.583
Any other little surprises
you'd like to share with us?

132
00:09:09.299 --> 00:09:10.505
No.

133
00:09:11.885 --> 00:09:14.877
Look. I haven't been a whitelighter
very long. okay?

134
00:09:15.055 --> 00:09:17.137
And healing. it's big.

135
00:09:17.307 --> 00:09:20.516
-And takes a while to learn how to do.
-Great. student-lighter.

136
00:09:20.685 --> 00:09:24.724
You could have told us about this.
like. I don't know. maybe a month ago?

137
00:09:24.898 --> 00:09:26.559
Well. I know one thing for sure.

138
00:09:26.733 --> 00:09:29.020
We're gonna stop
all this demon-fighting for a while.

139
00:09:29.235 --> 00:09:30.851
Wait. Why?

140
00:09:31.071 --> 00:09:34.359
PIPER: Can somebody please fold
the towels in the dryer when it's done?

141
00:09:34.532 --> 00:09:35.567
That's why.

142
00:09:35.784 --> 00:09:38.822
I put a casserole in the oven. You can
check it in about an hour or so.

143
00:09:38.995 --> 00:09:42.078
I will be at the club if you need me.
Have fun.

144
00:09:42.290 --> 00:09:43.325
[WYATT COOING]

145
00:09:43.500 --> 00:09:46.083
Oh. my God. She is so sad.

146
00:09:46.252 --> 00:09:48.539
Sad?
Where are you getting sad from?

147
00:09:48.755 --> 00:09:52.293
How about this? Three more demons.
then we can talk about taking a break.

148
00:09:52.509 --> 00:09:53.874
Do you have a quota or something?

149
00:09:54.094 --> 00:09:55.300
I've told you this before.

150
00:09:55.470 --> 00:09:58.337
I know from future knowledge that
a demon is gonna come after Wyatt.

151
00:09:58.515 --> 00:10:00.381
These are all
just pre-emptive strikes.

152
00:10:00.600 --> 00:10:02.511
Okay. Look. Chris. we like you a lot.

153
00:10:02.685 --> 00:10:04.892
But we've been doing this
a lot longer than you have.

154
00:10:05.063 --> 00:10:09.933
Trust me. you have to pace yourself
and you gotta let us have a life.

155
00:10:10.110 --> 00:10:13.068
Speaking of which. I have to go
get ready for my lunch date.

156
00:10:13.238 --> 00:10:15.320
Oh. I didn't know your boss
was back in town.

157
00:10:15.782 --> 00:10:17.113
No. it's not with Jason.

158
00:10:17.283 --> 00:10:20.526
It's with Chad. the DJ.
who I'm not really interested in.

159
00:10:20.954 --> 00:10:22.911
Two demons.
How about that? Two?

160
00:10:23.123 --> 00:10:26.787
No. Chris. and especially not until
we figure out what's wrong with Piper.

161
00:10:26.960 --> 00:10:28.871
And more importantly.
Piper's powers.

162
00:10:29.087 --> 00:10:31.795
I swear. I think Leo did something
to her before he left.

163
00:10:32.006 --> 00:10:36.091
You know what? I think it's about time
we orb him down here and ask him.

164
00:10:36.261 --> 00:10:38.981
- I don't think that's possible.
PHOEBE: Well. then make it possible.

165
00:10:39.013 --> 00:10:41.004
Even if he doesn't care
about Piper as his wife.

166
00:10:41.182 --> 00:10:44.675
as an Elder. he at the least should care
about what happened to her powers.

167
00:10:45.145 --> 00:10:47.136
-I can't.
-Yeah. you can.

168
00:10:47.313 --> 00:10:49.975
You just go up there and tell him
to get his butt back down here.

169
00:10:50.608 --> 00:10:52.394
That's not why I can't.

170
00:10:52.610 --> 00:10:56.148
I didn't wanna tell you this because
I didn't wanna worry you two but...

171
00:10:57.699 --> 00:10:59.281
Leo's missing.

172
00:10:59.450 --> 00:11:02.659
-What?
-Missing? How long?

173
00:11:03.913 --> 00:11:06.075
Since the last time we saw him.

174
00:11:09.002 --> 00:11:12.996
Anyways. the Elders
think he's been... kidnapped.

175
00:11:13.840 --> 00:11:15.376
By whom?

176
00:11:18.219 --> 00:11:19.550
[YELLING]

177
00:11:19.762 --> 00:11:22.003
SOLDIER 1:
Go! Go!

178
00:11:22.182 --> 00:11:23.513
[SOLDIER GRUNTING]

179
00:11:24.267 --> 00:11:25.428
SOLDIER 2:
They got Kruger!

180
00:11:31.399 --> 00:11:32.434
Who?

181
00:11:33.568 --> 00:11:35.525
-What the...?
-Shh.

182
00:11:35.945 --> 00:11:38.277
It's all right.
You don't have to be afraid.

183
00:11:38.698 --> 00:11:40.609
You're one of the chosen few.

184
00:11:50.376 --> 00:11:51.707
MIST:
Don't worry.

185
00:11:51.920 --> 00:11:54.207
I promise you'll understand
soon enough.

186
00:12:15.735 --> 00:12:17.567
SHEILA: You're amazing. Piper.
PIPER: Sorry?

187
00:12:17.737 --> 00:12:19.648
I mean. seriously.
I don't know how you do it.

188
00:12:19.822 --> 00:12:22.029
I mean. I could barely
take care of myself

189
00:12:22.200 --> 00:12:24.817
when little Darryl was a baby.
let alone run a daycare.

190
00:12:25.036 --> 00:12:28.028
Well. you know. nobody was using
the club during the day anyway.

191
00:12:28.206 --> 00:12:31.699
and I was running out of room at home
with all of Wyatt's play dates.

192
00:12:31.918 --> 00:12:33.750
Well. I think it's great.

193
00:12:33.920 --> 00:12:37.413
Really. I mean. especially
with everything you're going through.

194
00:12:41.219 --> 00:12:42.254
What?

195
00:12:43.137 --> 00:12:45.253
Sheila's been a little
concerned about you lately.

196
00:12:46.057 --> 00:12:47.968
You know. with Leo and all.

197
00:12:48.184 --> 00:12:50.346
I can't even imagine
how hard it must be for you.

198
00:12:50.561 --> 00:12:52.097
SHEILA:
Do you ever even talk to him?

199
00:12:52.272 --> 00:12:54.434
Oh. no. It's probably
against the rules.

200
00:12:54.607 --> 00:12:56.939
But. you know.
no use crying over spilt milk.

201
00:12:57.151 --> 00:13:00.314
And besides. you know.
I just gotta push ahead for Wyatt.

202
00:13:02.615 --> 00:13:04.606
Well. better get these treats
to the little ones.

203
00:13:04.784 --> 00:13:06.821
Is Darryl Jr. staying late?

204
00:13:07.036 --> 00:13:08.618
-Yeah.
-Yeah. yeah.

205
00:13:08.830 --> 00:13:09.991
Super.

206
00:13:11.874 --> 00:13:14.332
PIPER: Hey. guys. have fun.
Coming through.

207
00:13:14.877 --> 00:13:17.414
I gotta get back to the station.

208
00:13:19.090 --> 00:13:20.797
PIPER: Hi. guys.
-Hey.

209
00:13:21.009 --> 00:13:23.842
-Hi.
-What's the matter?

210
00:13:25.513 --> 00:13:28.130
-Sorry?
-Something's bothering you. I can tell.

211
00:13:29.767 --> 00:13:31.974
-Phoebe?
-What?

212
00:13:32.145 --> 00:13:33.226
Oh. sorry.

213
00:13:33.438 --> 00:13:35.770
So. you know.
Piper's doing fine. huh?

214
00:13:35.982 --> 00:13:38.098
Yeah. but you don't think she is.

215
00:13:39.652 --> 00:13:42.861
Don't mind her.
she's just being a little annoying.

216
00:13:43.031 --> 00:13:45.068
Would you excuse us for a second?

217
00:13:45.616 --> 00:13:47.778
-Yeah. sure.
-Yeah.

218
00:13:47.994 --> 00:13:49.735
SHEILA: See you later.
PHOEBE: Bye.

219
00:13:49.954 --> 00:13:51.820
What is going on with you?

220
00:13:52.040 --> 00:13:53.201
I don't know. it's weird.

221
00:13:53.374 --> 00:13:57.459
Lately. I've just been feeling
a lot of weird vibes.

222
00:13:57.628 --> 00:13:58.709
I don't know what it is.

223
00:13:58.921 --> 00:14:01.458
Vibes. Hmm.

224
00:14:01.674 --> 00:14:03.756
Check it out.
I can really. really only deal

225
00:14:03.926 --> 00:14:06.884
-with one whacked out sister at a time.
-Got it.

226
00:14:08.639 --> 00:14:10.505
Piper?

227
00:14:10.725 --> 00:14:11.840
Piper. you got a minute?

228
00:14:12.060 --> 00:14:15.473
-Can it wait?
-No. actually. it can't.

229
00:14:15.646 --> 00:14:17.933
-It's about Leo.
-Oh. did he call?

230
00:14:18.149 --> 00:14:19.184
Not exactly.

231
00:14:19.400 --> 00:14:22.438
There's no easy way to break this
so I'm just gonna come out and say it.

232
00:14:23.905 --> 00:14:25.395
Leo's missing.

233
00:14:25.573 --> 00:14:29.658
We found out the Elders haven't heard
from him since he left to join them.

234
00:14:30.411 --> 00:14:31.446
Wow.

235
00:14:33.247 --> 00:14:35.409
So did he happen
to say anything to you

236
00:14:35.625 --> 00:14:38.413
the last time you saw him
that could potentially help?

237
00:14:38.628 --> 00:14:40.744
No. All I remember him saying

238
00:14:40.922 --> 00:14:44.756
is that he was leaving to become
an Elder and I wished him good luck.

239
00:14:44.967 --> 00:14:46.833
That's it?
That was your big goodbye?

240
00:14:47.053 --> 00:14:48.885
Yeah. as far as I can remember.

241
00:14:49.055 --> 00:14:52.468
But I wouldn't worry about it too much.
He'll turn up sooner or later.

242
00:14:52.642 --> 00:14:53.677
Excuse me.

243
00:14:55.353 --> 00:14:57.936
So much for that shocking
her back into reality. huh?

244
00:14:58.147 --> 00:15:00.309
Unfortunately.
I think only Leo can do that.

245
00:15:33.766 --> 00:15:35.632
[YELLING]

246
00:15:46.070 --> 00:15:47.401
[MAN LAUGHING]

247
00:15:49.866 --> 00:15:51.948
VALKYRIE:
Greetings. Mist.

248
00:15:56.706 --> 00:15:58.367
VALKYRIE:
You under-rotated.

249
00:15:58.541 --> 00:16:00.532
Now watch.

250
00:16:12.388 --> 00:16:13.844
You were gone a while. Mist.

251
00:16:14.015 --> 00:16:15.130
I was beginning to worry.

252
00:16:15.308 --> 00:16:17.720
I wanted you to be pleased.

253
00:16:28.154 --> 00:16:29.940
Cute.

254
00:16:30.156 --> 00:16:31.612
But can he fight?

255
00:16:31.824 --> 00:16:32.985
Like no other.

256
00:16:33.201 --> 00:16:34.362
FREYJA:
We'll see.

257
00:16:34.911 --> 00:16:36.822
Am I in heaven?

258
00:16:37.455 --> 00:16:38.741
Warrior heaven.

259
00:16:39.165 --> 00:16:42.328
Until I see how well you do
against our champion. anyway.

260
00:17:09.529 --> 00:17:10.644
What do you want from me?

261
00:17:10.863 --> 00:17:12.479
We want you to fight.

262
00:17:12.698 --> 00:17:13.733
[SWORD UNSHEATHING]

263
00:18:03.708 --> 00:18:05.369
He fought well enough.

264
00:18:05.543 --> 00:18:08.706
Heal him. Get him into training.

265
00:18:12.300 --> 00:18:14.837
VALKYRIE: Come.
SOLDIER: What about me?

266
00:18:15.011 --> 00:18:17.252
I don't belong here and you know it!

267
00:18:17.471 --> 00:18:20.054
No? You're an Elder. aren't you?

268
00:18:21.434 --> 00:18:23.516
You have much to teach
my warriors.

269
00:18:51.589 --> 00:18:54.877
Where exactly are you trying
to find Leo? Jupiter?

270
00:18:55.051 --> 00:18:56.541
When an Elder gets kidnapped.

271
00:18:56.719 --> 00:18:59.211
they're probably not just gonna
take him to Chinatown. right?

272
00:18:59.388 --> 00:19:01.755
I think everything is game.
even the cosmos.

273
00:19:01.932 --> 00:19:04.094
Still. I don't see how the crystal's
gonna find him.

274
00:19:04.268 --> 00:19:06.805
especially not without something
of his to focus it better.

275
00:19:07.980 --> 00:19:10.096
I've got one of his plaid shirts.

276
00:19:10.316 --> 00:19:13.058
I was thinking something
a little more special than that.

277
00:19:13.277 --> 00:19:15.814
Leo loved those shirts.
His entire closet's full of them.

278
00:19:20.034 --> 00:19:21.069
What's your problem?

279
00:19:22.161 --> 00:19:25.153
-Huh?
-You're nervous. I can feel it.

280
00:19:25.331 --> 00:19:27.163
Watch your vibes.

281
00:19:27.375 --> 00:19:31.585
I just think you guys should be
focusing on helping Piper. not Leo.

282
00:19:31.754 --> 00:19:33.394
- Ha! I was right.
PAIGE: Hey. finding Leo

283
00:19:33.506 --> 00:19:35.292
could help us with Piper.

284
00:19:35.466 --> 00:19:39.255
Well. then you better find another way.
because you are not gonna find him.

285
00:19:42.515 --> 00:19:44.802
I mean. you haven't found him yet.
have you?

286
00:19:45.726 --> 00:19:48.559
I'm telling you. just leave
it up to the Elders. all right?

287
00:19:48.729 --> 00:19:51.687
-Just let it go.
-Let it go? He's Wyatt's father.

288
00:19:51.899 --> 00:19:53.890
-And our brother-in-law.
-Ex-brother-in-law.

289
00:19:54.068 --> 00:19:57.060
I'm just trying to get you two to focus
on your sister here. That's all.

290
00:19:57.238 --> 00:20:00.481
Because with her powers messed up.
you guys are all at risk.

291
00:20:02.993 --> 00:20:04.449
-He's right.
-I know.

292
00:20:04.620 --> 00:20:07.783
But if Leo did do something
to block Piper's pain.

293
00:20:07.998 --> 00:20:09.488
how do we unblock it without him?

294
00:20:09.667 --> 00:20:12.284
-A magical laxative.
-Okay. Ew.

295
00:20:12.461 --> 00:20:15.954
But think about it. If we can write
a spell to help her remember her pain.

296
00:20:16.173 --> 00:20:18.881
PAIGE: I don't know.
it could even help us find Leo.

297
00:20:21.345 --> 00:20:23.086
Who are you calling. Spells "R" Us?

298
00:20:23.264 --> 00:20:24.800
No. I'm calling the Bayview Café.

299
00:20:24.974 --> 00:20:28.092
I'm gonna cancel my lunch date
with Chad. which I'm already late for.

300
00:20:28.269 --> 00:20:29.304
<i>Bayview Café.</i>

301
00:20:29.478 --> 00:20:32.391
Hi. can I speak to Chad Carson. please?
I was supposed to meet him for...

302
00:20:32.565 --> 00:20:34.459
WOMAN [ON PHONE]:
<i>Yes. he couldn't make it today.</i>

303
00:20:34.483 --> 00:20:36.474
-What?
<i>-He called and he canceled.</i>

304
00:20:36.694 --> 00:20:38.401
-He canceled?
<i>-Yes. he canceled.</i>

305
00:20:38.571 --> 00:20:39.971
Are you sure?
He didn't even call...

306
00:20:40.114 --> 00:20:43.857
<i>He told us
to let you know he's very sorry.</i>

307
00:20:44.243 --> 00:20:45.779
Ha!

308
00:20:46.579 --> 00:20:47.694
He stood me up.

309
00:20:48.456 --> 00:20:50.493
Wait. weren't you just calling
to cancel on him?

310
00:20:50.708 --> 00:20:52.699
Yeah. but I called him.
That's canceling.

311
00:20:52.877 --> 00:20:55.414
He called the restaurant.
That's standing up.

312
00:20:56.630 --> 00:20:58.337
-Oh.
-This doesn't make any sense.

313
00:20:58.507 --> 00:20:59.588
I don't understand.

314
00:20:59.759 --> 00:21:02.922
He liked me.
he really liked me. I felt it.

315
00:21:03.137 --> 00:21:07.927
Well. excuse me. but it didn't even
seem like your heart was in it anyway.

316
00:21:09.727 --> 00:21:11.388
Where you going?
We have a spell to write!

317
00:21:11.604 --> 00:21:13.345
And I have a DJ to grill!

318
00:21:16.692 --> 00:21:18.228
COOK:
All right. here you go. Chad.

319
00:21:18.402 --> 00:21:20.188
Thanks. Billy.

320
00:21:20.780 --> 00:21:21.861
PHOEBE:
Hey.

321
00:21:22.031 --> 00:21:24.272
I hear they have hot dogs
at the Bayview Café.

322
00:21:24.492 --> 00:21:26.278
Phoebe. what are you doing here?

323
00:21:26.452 --> 00:21:28.568
That's funny. I was about to ask
you the same thing.

324
00:21:28.788 --> 00:21:30.574
Listen. I can explain.

325
00:21:30.790 --> 00:21:32.827
That's good.
because that's why I'm here.

326
00:21:33.042 --> 00:21:35.374
I was just hoping you could
help me understand something

327
00:21:35.544 --> 00:21:38.252
that's baffled women
since the beginning of time.

328
00:21:39.590 --> 00:21:42.127
Why don't men call
after they ask us out?

329
00:21:42.301 --> 00:21:44.042
And why do they cancel
at the last minute.

330
00:21:44.220 --> 00:21:47.303
and even worse. stand us up?

331
00:21:47.515 --> 00:21:50.849
Look. I'm sorry but I had something
really important come up.

332
00:21:53.854 --> 00:21:56.312
-Are you intimidated by me?
-What?

333
00:21:56.524 --> 00:21:59.312
Because you weren't intimidated
by me when you asked me out.

334
00:21:59.527 --> 00:22:01.393
Hold on. you asked me out.
remember?

335
00:22:01.612 --> 00:22:03.979
Oh. wait. Are you saying
that you didn't want me though?

336
00:22:04.156 --> 00:22:07.694
-Because I know you did. I felt it.
-Wait a minute.

337
00:22:11.038 --> 00:22:12.904
You don't like successful women.

338
00:22:14.750 --> 00:22:16.081
I gotta go.

339
00:22:16.293 --> 00:22:20.036
Wait. are you telling me that everything
that I've worked so hard for in my life.

340
00:22:20.214 --> 00:22:24.128
everything I fought to achieve.
makes me less attractive to men?

341
00:22:24.343 --> 00:22:27.051
Because if that's what you're saying.
I just...

342
00:22:27.263 --> 00:22:28.594
[CHILD CRYING]

343
00:22:28.806 --> 00:22:31.798
It just hurts. It hurts so much.

344
00:22:32.017 --> 00:22:34.725
It hurts so much. Mommy!

345
00:22:34.937 --> 00:22:37.269
Don't you think
you're overreacting just a little?

346
00:22:37.481 --> 00:22:38.687
No. I don't!

347
00:22:40.943 --> 00:22:43.025
Actually. yeah. I do.

348
00:22:43.237 --> 00:22:47.447
- It hurts so much. Mommy.
MOTHER: I know it does.

349
00:22:49.952 --> 00:22:52.489
Sir. what does it matter
when I bring the dogs home?

350
00:22:52.663 --> 00:22:56.201
Their owners aren't there. That's why
I got the job in the first place.

351
00:22:56.417 --> 00:23:00.331
Why don't you go hump a dog?
Did you ever think of that?

352
00:23:00.504 --> 00:23:02.040
No. not you. sir.

353
00:23:02.256 --> 00:23:04.964
Look. you know.
when I came to the agency.

354
00:23:05.134 --> 00:23:11.426
I really went with the idea that I would
be helping people. not animals.

355
00:23:11.640 --> 00:23:14.098
And what I really mean
to say is that it's...

356
00:23:14.268 --> 00:23:18.227
Sir. it is time for me
to strike out on my own.

357
00:23:18.439 --> 00:23:20.021
[DOGS BARKING]

358
00:23:20.232 --> 00:23:23.190
Yeah. I'll have the dogs
back in an hour.

359
00:23:24.486 --> 00:23:27.353
CHRIS: <i>Piper's home!</i>
-Coming.

360
00:23:27.573 --> 00:23:28.608
[BABY CRYING]

361
00:23:28.782 --> 00:23:30.272
PAIGE:
Hey. who's that?

362
00:23:30.451 --> 00:23:31.782
Ask her.

363
00:23:31.952 --> 00:23:34.410
PIPER:
Hi. how's it going?

364
00:23:34.580 --> 00:23:36.662
How's it going?

365
00:23:36.832 --> 00:23:37.947
What are you doing?

366
00:23:38.125 --> 00:23:39.741
Whose babies are these?

367
00:23:39.919 --> 00:23:41.034
PIPER:
Hi.

368
00:23:41.211 --> 00:23:43.543
Well. their mommies
couldn't pick them up in time.

369
00:23:43.714 --> 00:23:46.046
so I offered to bring
them home for a while.

370
00:23:46.216 --> 00:23:48.878
Oh. you did?

371
00:23:49.053 --> 00:23:50.714
What about. you know. Leo?

372
00:23:50.888 --> 00:23:53.380
I don't know. what about him?

373
00:23:53.599 --> 00:23:56.808
PIPER:
Look. Wyatt. look who's here.

374
00:23:56.977 --> 00:23:59.594
Another friend for you to play with.

375
00:23:59.772 --> 00:24:02.184
-Is that the memory spell?
-Yeah.

376
00:24:03.275 --> 00:24:05.232
PIPER: And she can stay
as long as she likes.

377
00:24:05.444 --> 00:24:06.855
Cast it.

378
00:24:08.656 --> 00:24:11.318
<i>"Powers and emotions tied
A witch's heart is where it hides</i>

379
00:24:11.492 --> 00:24:15.156
<i>Help her through her agony
Bless her with her memory"</i>

380
00:24:18.165 --> 00:24:21.874
Piper. you okay?

381
00:24:23.420 --> 00:24:25.502
I'm sorry. do I know you?

382
00:24:26.924 --> 00:24:27.959
Very funny.

383
00:24:28.968 --> 00:24:30.709
Oh. cute.

384
00:24:32.388 --> 00:24:33.423
Yours?

385
00:24:33.639 --> 00:24:35.380
No. yours.

386
00:24:35.599 --> 00:24:38.011
Mine? Well. what do you mean?

387
00:24:38.185 --> 00:24:40.973
Wait. who am I?

388
00:24:41.146 --> 00:24:43.638
What am I doing here?

389
00:24:43.857 --> 00:24:47.066
Great. Paige. you didn't restore
her memory. you erased it.

390
00:24:47.277 --> 00:24:49.814
That's impossible.
It's a good spell. I know it.

391
00:24:50.322 --> 00:24:54.316
Unless it interacted badly
with Leo's magic.

392
00:24:54.535 --> 00:24:55.900
[FLY BUZZING]

393
00:24:57.121 --> 00:24:59.658
What happened?
How did that happen?

394
00:25:00.416 --> 00:25:02.532
It's okay.
You're gonna be okay.

395
00:25:02.710 --> 00:25:05.452
Just don't point at anything. okay?
Just keep your hands down.

396
00:25:05.629 --> 00:25:08.166
CHRIS:
Like this: Okay?

397
00:25:08.340 --> 00:25:10.456
Can somebody please
tell me what's going on?

398
00:25:11.093 --> 00:25:14.302
We're gonna tell you that.
just as soon as we know ourselves.

399
00:25:15.055 --> 00:25:18.468
Okay. you come in here.
and you have a seat.

400
00:25:18.642 --> 00:25:20.007
and take a load off.

401
00:25:20.185 --> 00:25:22.096
Yeah. and keep those arms down.

402
00:25:22.479 --> 00:25:23.810
PAIGE:
Oh. my goodness.

403
00:25:24.023 --> 00:25:27.687
Don't freak out. because magic got us
into this and magic will get us out.

404
00:25:28.152 --> 00:25:29.813
[WYATT CRYING]

405
00:25:36.201 --> 00:25:37.612
- Did you see that?
CHRIS: See what?

406
00:25:37.828 --> 00:25:40.946
-Wyatt. he orbed his pacifier.
-What?

407
00:25:42.541 --> 00:25:44.532
I think I know how to find Leo.

408
00:25:44.710 --> 00:25:47.828
Leo? Will you please
forget about Leo?

409
00:25:48.547 --> 00:25:50.788
Oh. Piper. hi!

410
00:25:50.966 --> 00:25:52.377
You're never gonna believe this.

411
00:25:52.593 --> 00:25:54.049
I think I have a new power.

412
00:25:54.261 --> 00:25:56.753
It would certainly explain
a lot of my weird behavior lately.

413
00:25:56.930 --> 00:25:58.170
like why I wanted to date Chad.

414
00:25:58.348 --> 00:26:01.386
and why my advice
has been so amazingly accurate.

415
00:26:02.186 --> 00:26:04.848
I know. this is huge. right? Huge.

416
00:26:05.064 --> 00:26:07.476
So. what's my new power you ask?
Oh. I'll tell you.

417
00:26:07.649 --> 00:26:10.482
Do you remember that empath
we helped a couple of years ago?

418
00:26:10.652 --> 00:26:13.235
PHOEBE: That guy that could feel
what other people were feeling?

419
00:26:13.447 --> 00:26:14.653
-Phoebe.
-Just a sec.

420
00:26:14.823 --> 00:26:16.405
I think that's what I am now.

421
00:26:17.076 --> 00:26:18.612
An empath.

422
00:26:18.786 --> 00:26:21.198
I am an empath.

423
00:26:21.371 --> 00:26:22.782
That's my new power.

424
00:26:22.956 --> 00:26:25.744
Or at least an advancement
of my premonition power. I don't know.

425
00:26:25.959 --> 00:26:27.666
Neither does she. I'm afraid.

426
00:26:27.878 --> 00:26:29.539
CHRIS:
Know. that is. anything.

427
00:26:29.755 --> 00:26:31.245
Paige erased her memory.

428
00:26:32.883 --> 00:26:34.749
Can you blow things up too?

429
00:26:36.637 --> 00:26:38.628
Oh. boy.

430
00:26:38.806 --> 00:26:39.887
Paige!

431
00:26:45.646 --> 00:26:48.229
What did you do to our sister?

432
00:26:48.857 --> 00:26:50.268
Oh. you poor dear.

433
00:26:50.484 --> 00:26:52.771
You feel awful about it. don't you?

434
00:26:52.986 --> 00:26:54.021
I'm so sorry.

435
00:26:55.197 --> 00:26:58.735
-Thanks. I think.
-That's it?

436
00:26:58.909 --> 00:27:02.118
That's all the ass-kicking you'll dole
out? You're supposed to be sisters.

437
00:27:02.329 --> 00:27:04.366
She's clearly devastated about this.

438
00:27:04.581 --> 00:27:07.699
You can't let her off the hook. You
need enough guilt to get her to fix it.

439
00:27:08.836 --> 00:27:10.122
I think I just fixed it.

440
00:27:10.337 --> 00:27:11.919
PAIGE:
I think we just found Leo.

441
00:27:12.131 --> 00:27:14.793
PHOEBE: "We"?
-Yep. Wyatt and me.

442
00:27:14.967 --> 00:27:18.301
I mean. nothing's more important
to Leo than him. right?

443
00:27:18.512 --> 00:27:20.128
PAIGE:
Oh. there you go. big boy.

444
00:27:21.932 --> 00:27:24.219
-Let's go.
-Go? Go where?

445
00:27:24.393 --> 00:27:26.430
It's pointing to the middle
of the Indian Ocean.

446
00:27:26.645 --> 00:27:28.477
There must be something there.
I trust Wyatt.

447
00:27:28.689 --> 00:27:30.049
- No. this is crazy.
PHOEBE: Chris.

448
00:27:30.190 --> 00:27:32.101
she's feeling really
strongly about this.

449
00:27:34.820 --> 00:27:36.402
I have a new power.

450
00:27:36.572 --> 00:27:38.563
I'll explain on the way.

451
00:27:38.740 --> 00:27:40.481
Hey. can you take the dogs
back for me?

452
00:27:40.659 --> 00:27:42.900
-The addresses are in the book.
-No. there's no way.

453
00:27:49.459 --> 00:27:52.417
If anyone should be protecting
themselves. it's me from you.

454
00:28:14.443 --> 00:28:18.653
It's so beautiful here. it's like paradise.
But why isn't it on the map?

455
00:28:18.822 --> 00:28:20.904
They obviously don't want
anyone to know it exists.

456
00:28:21.074 --> 00:28:24.362
Like the island has some sort
of magical camouflage or something.

457
00:28:24.536 --> 00:28:26.652
Yeah. well.
that's a hell of a lot of magic.

458
00:28:26.830 --> 00:28:28.366
MAN:
Over there!

459
00:28:40.427 --> 00:28:43.590
Well. that was close.
I hope they're not looking for us.

460
00:28:59.321 --> 00:29:00.356
Anything?

461
00:29:00.572 --> 00:29:01.778
Phoebe. Paige.

462
00:29:01.990 --> 00:29:04.277
Leo! Oh. my God.

463
00:29:04.493 --> 00:29:06.029
PAIGE:
I can't believe it.

464
00:29:06.203 --> 00:29:08.114
I can't tell you how good
it is to see you guys.

465
00:29:08.288 --> 00:29:10.655
-Hey. you cut your hair.
-Yeah. you like it?

466
00:29:10.874 --> 00:29:13.036
PAIGE: Hello. people.
PHOEBE: Oh.

467
00:29:13.252 --> 00:29:14.788
What are you doing in here anyway?

468
00:29:15.003 --> 00:29:17.620
Somebody put me here. that's what.
Watch out!

469
00:29:39.903 --> 00:29:40.938
Oh. thank you.

470
00:29:44.658 --> 00:29:46.774
Wow. Leo. I didn't know
you had it in you.

471
00:29:46.994 --> 00:29:48.029
I've changed.

472
00:29:48.203 --> 00:29:51.662
Get out before the Valkyries find you.
If you orbed here. they've been alerted.

473
00:29:52.124 --> 00:29:54.365
Valkyries? Who are they.
and what do they want with you?

474
00:29:54.543 --> 00:29:56.534
But you can't orb out from here.
it's protected.

475
00:29:56.712 --> 00:29:59.545
You need to get out of here.
Now go! Run!

476
00:29:59.715 --> 00:30:00.876
We'll be back.

477
00:30:11.560 --> 00:30:14.518
I told you. I don't belong here.

478
00:30:21.611 --> 00:30:22.897
[DOG GROWLING]

479
00:30:23.071 --> 00:30:26.280
You could have been killed. you know
that? What were you thinking?

480
00:30:26.491 --> 00:30:30.359
We were thinking of finding Leo. which
we actually did. if that matters to you.

481
00:30:30.537 --> 00:30:32.869
What was up with that skirt
he was wearing?

482
00:30:33.040 --> 00:30:34.451
At least the skirt wasn't plaid.

483
00:30:34.624 --> 00:30:35.705
[LAUGHING]

484
00:30:35.917 --> 00:30:39.285
I don't believe this. It's like neither of
you guys are taking this very seriously.

485
00:30:40.922 --> 00:30:44.836
-Hey. do you mind?
-I can't help it if he doesn't like you.

486
00:30:45.010 --> 00:30:46.421
You were supposed
to take him home.

487
00:30:46.636 --> 00:30:48.593
I tried. but the owners weren't there.

488
00:30:48.764 --> 00:30:51.472
Besides. the dog.
he's not my job. he's yours.

489
00:30:51.683 --> 00:30:53.094
I know. don't remind me.

490
00:30:53.268 --> 00:30:55.760
Hey. Oscar. lay down.

491
00:30:56.396 --> 00:30:58.057
[DOG WHIMPERING]

492
00:31:00.859 --> 00:31:02.475
Look. Paige. I think he likes you.

493
00:31:02.694 --> 00:31:03.809
PAIGE:
Yeah. great.

494
00:31:04.029 --> 00:31:05.770
Don't tell me you can read
his feelings too.

495
00:31:05.947 --> 00:31:09.406
No. but if I start
licking your toes. run.

496
00:31:09.576 --> 00:31:10.611
Where's Piper?

497
00:31:10.827 --> 00:31:13.194
I put her in her room. hoping
that it might jog her memory.

498
00:31:13.372 --> 00:31:15.079
since nobody else
seems to be trying to.

499
00:31:16.041 --> 00:31:17.281
Here it is.

500
00:31:17.459 --> 00:31:20.042
"Valkyries. a powerful race
of demigoddesses

501
00:31:20.212 --> 00:31:22.419
who scout the battlegrounds
for dying warriors..."

502
00:31:22.589 --> 00:31:24.149
"... then take their souls to Valhalla.

503
00:31:24.257 --> 00:31:26.840
where they prepare them
for the final world battle."

504
00:31:27.052 --> 00:31:28.508
PAIGE:
Valkyries. huh?

505
00:31:29.596 --> 00:31:30.757
Does that mean they're good?

506
00:31:32.057 --> 00:31:33.764
How can they be good
if they've got Leo?

507
00:31:33.975 --> 00:31:37.138
And how did they even get Leo?
He's not a dying warrior. he's an Elder.

508
00:31:37.813 --> 00:31:39.724
Why don't you guys
concentrate on helping Piper.

509
00:31:39.898 --> 00:31:42.356
I'm gonna fill in the Elders
and see what they want to do.

510
00:31:42.526 --> 00:31:45.143
Chris. we don't have time.
We have to go back for Leo now.

511
00:31:45.362 --> 00:31:47.103
Why? Doesn't sound
like he's in trouble.

512
00:31:47.697 --> 00:31:49.313
He's only stuck in a cage.

513
00:31:49.533 --> 00:31:51.386
They tried to kill us
when we tried to save him.

514
00:31:51.410 --> 00:31:53.617
My point exactly. Too dangerous.
You're not going back.

515
00:31:53.787 --> 00:31:55.778
Wait. let me get this straight.

516
00:31:55.956 --> 00:31:58.368
Are you telling me that you'd
rather just let Leo rot there.

517
00:31:58.542 --> 00:31:59.657
is that what you're saying?

518
00:31:59.876 --> 00:32:01.742
-No. but...
-He needs our help.

519
00:32:01.920 --> 00:32:04.708
Not to mention he may be
the only way we have to save Piper.

520
00:32:06.883 --> 00:32:09.170
You can't orb into Valhalla
undetected.

521
00:32:09.344 --> 00:32:11.961
The only way to get there safely
is with a Valkyrie's pendant.

522
00:32:15.058 --> 00:32:17.891
But that still won't get you close to Leo.
He's too well-guarded now.

523
00:32:18.061 --> 00:32:19.142
How do you know all this?

524
00:32:19.688 --> 00:32:21.474
I've crossed paths
with Valkyries before...

525
00:32:22.357 --> 00:32:23.392
...in the future.

526
00:32:23.608 --> 00:32:26.600
Anyway. I can get you pendants.
but the only way to get close to Leo

527
00:32:26.778 --> 00:32:28.769
is by proving to the Valkyries
you're one of them.

528
00:32:28.947 --> 00:32:30.483
How are we supposed to do that?

529
00:32:30.949 --> 00:32:33.361
Easy. just arrive
with a warrior's soul.

530
00:32:33.577 --> 00:32:35.739
Oh. easy.

531
00:32:35.912 --> 00:32:38.199
Where are we supposed to find
a warrior's soul?

532
00:32:38.999 --> 00:32:40.740
Beats me.

533
00:32:43.879 --> 00:32:45.244
[GUNSHOTS SOUNDING]

534
00:32:51.052 --> 00:32:53.919
It's all right.
you don't have to be afraid.

535
00:32:54.139 --> 00:32:55.470
You're a brave warrior.

536
00:32:55.682 --> 00:32:56.968
I'll take care of you.

537
00:32:57.392 --> 00:33:00.180
I don't think so. Le yea. Not this time.

538
00:33:00.353 --> 00:33:01.514
What are you doing here?

539
00:33:01.730 --> 00:33:03.596
My plans have changed.
unfortunately.

540
00:33:03.773 --> 00:33:05.935
The witches found Leo
sooner than I would have liked.

541
00:33:06.401 --> 00:33:09.519
That's not my problem.
We kept our end of the deal.

542
00:33:09.738 --> 00:33:11.320
I know.

543
00:33:11.490 --> 00:33:13.447
And I'm forever grateful.

544
00:33:13.617 --> 00:33:15.608
But I can't risk them
finding out what I'm up to.

545
00:33:17.162 --> 00:33:18.994
I'm truly sorry.

546
00:33:37.974 --> 00:33:39.260
Forgive me.

547
00:33:59.287 --> 00:34:03.451
Officer down. 8th Avenue sewer.
We need an ambulance.

548
00:34:03.625 --> 00:34:06.458
WOMAN [OVER RADIO]: <i>Attention all
units in the vicinity of 8th Avenue.</i>

549
00:34:06.628 --> 00:34:09.495
<i>We have an officer down.
I repeat. we have an officer down.</i>

550
00:34:13.635 --> 00:34:16.798
- You ain't got nothing on me.
DARRYL: Shut up.

551
00:34:17.889 --> 00:34:19.596
Get in there.

552
00:34:23.270 --> 00:34:25.432
DARRYL: Wait here.
-Yeah. like I'm going anywhere.

553
00:34:25.647 --> 00:34:28.935
Are you out of your mind?
What are you doing here?

554
00:34:29.109 --> 00:34:30.149
Darryl. we need your help.

555
00:34:30.318 --> 00:34:33.060
Does this have anything to do with
you asking Sheila to watch Wyatt?

556
00:34:33.238 --> 00:34:35.570
-She just called.
-Yes. but we don't have a lot of time.

557
00:34:35.740 --> 00:34:37.071
-It's about Leo.
-You found him?

558
00:34:37.242 --> 00:34:39.734
-Actually. we did.
-We need your help to save him.

559
00:34:39.953 --> 00:34:41.990
Sure. you know that.
Just ask. Anything.

560
00:34:42.163 --> 00:34:45.326
Great. We just need to borrow
your soul for a couple of hours.

561
00:34:45.500 --> 00:34:46.581
We'll get it right back.

562
00:34:46.793 --> 00:34:49.410
It's perfectly safe really.
Your body will just slip into a coma

563
00:34:49.588 --> 00:34:51.499
and as long
as we get your soul back in time...

564
00:34:51.673 --> 00:34:53.789
-Which we will.
-...you'll be fine.

565
00:34:53.967 --> 00:34:56.129
Just a little headache. that's all.

566
00:34:56.303 --> 00:34:57.964
What do you say?

567
00:35:01.057 --> 00:35:02.172
You're serious. aren't you?

568
00:35:02.684 --> 00:35:05.016
Please. Darryl. it's the only way
we can save Leo.

569
00:35:06.187 --> 00:35:07.973
No. I ain't doing it.

570
00:35:08.189 --> 00:35:09.520
Darryl. please.

571
00:35:09.733 --> 00:35:11.189
No. absolutely not.

572
00:35:11.401 --> 00:35:13.142
DARRYL:
I love Leo like a brother.

573
00:35:13.361 --> 00:35:16.023
but you know. there is a limit
to what you can ask a man to do.

574
00:35:16.197 --> 00:35:17.733
And this is definitely over the limit.

575
00:35:17.949 --> 00:35:21.067
-Uh. Darryl?
-What?

576
00:35:26.374 --> 00:35:29.366
Oh. That's just great.

577
00:35:35.008 --> 00:35:37.375
I hope this works.

578
00:35:41.556 --> 00:35:45.390
CHRIS: Just remember everything
I told you and you'll be fine. okay?

579
00:35:56.655 --> 00:35:59.943
Okay we got the... Oh. my God.
what did you do to Piper?

580
00:36:00.158 --> 00:36:02.900
I turned her into a Valkyrie.
And convinced her she's one too.

581
00:36:04.412 --> 00:36:06.744
Actually it wasn't that hard really.
considering the fact

582
00:36:06.915 --> 00:36:09.407
-that her mind is basically a blank.
-Why?

583
00:36:09.584 --> 00:36:12.076
You might need the power of three
to get Leo out of Valhalla.

584
00:36:12.253 --> 00:36:15.371
And this is the only way
you're gonna get her into Valhalla.

585
00:36:15.590 --> 00:36:18.127
Well. if Piper ever gets
her memory back. she's gonna kill you.

586
00:36:18.593 --> 00:36:20.004
-Why?
-Because she hates wearing

587
00:36:20.178 --> 00:36:23.136
-those costumes as much as we do.
-Mm-hm.

588
00:36:23.348 --> 00:36:27.091
Yeah? Well. in that case.
you're gonna kill me too.

589
00:37:01.761 --> 00:37:02.796
Can I help you?

590
00:37:03.012 --> 00:37:04.298
We've brought you a warrior.

591
00:37:06.057 --> 00:37:08.674
-Warrior?
-Is there a problem?

592
00:37:15.442 --> 00:37:17.604
How come I don't recognize you?

593
00:37:20.238 --> 00:37:23.151
Perhaps you'll recognize this.

594
00:37:27.370 --> 00:37:31.455
A warrior's spirit. worthy of Valhalla.

595
00:37:36.796 --> 00:37:38.127
Well done.

596
00:37:46.222 --> 00:37:47.883
[DARRYL GRUNTS]

597
00:38:08.161 --> 00:38:11.244
Not a bad afterlife if you ask me.

598
00:38:14.209 --> 00:38:15.699
You're doing great. honey.

599
00:38:33.061 --> 00:38:35.143
Okay. I know how
we're gonna save Leo.

600
00:38:35.313 --> 00:38:36.769
but how are we gonna save Morris?

601
00:38:36.940 --> 00:38:38.977
I have no idea.
That's why they call it winging it.

602
00:38:39.150 --> 00:38:41.016
-What are you two talking about?
-Nothing.

603
00:38:53.289 --> 00:38:55.200
What are you waiting for? Attack!

604
00:38:59.671 --> 00:39:00.957
Aah!

605
00:39:03.758 --> 00:39:04.919
Leo?

606
00:39:07.637 --> 00:39:08.843
What are we gonna do?

607
00:39:09.055 --> 00:39:10.136
It's Piper.

608
00:39:10.306 --> 00:39:12.013
Her pain is back. Do something.

609
00:39:13.434 --> 00:39:15.266
Uh. kill him!

610
00:39:24.988 --> 00:39:26.444
-Take the fall!
-What fall?

611
00:39:28.908 --> 00:39:30.444
Stay down.

612
00:39:37.375 --> 00:39:39.161
What is he doing here?

613
00:39:39.335 --> 00:39:41.076
What are we doing here?

614
00:39:41.296 --> 00:39:42.457
Piper. shh.

615
00:39:43.631 --> 00:39:45.918
Ow. Do something.

616
00:39:48.219 --> 00:39:52.053
We just wanted to apologize
for sending you such a weak warrior.

617
00:39:52.223 --> 00:39:54.430
We can get rid of him for you.

618
00:39:54.642 --> 00:39:56.349
Get rid of him?

619
00:39:57.061 --> 00:39:58.972
Yeah. you know. like.

620
00:39:59.147 --> 00:40:04.563
send his spirit on
to the hereafter... or something.

621
00:40:06.696 --> 00:40:08.528
Very well.

622
00:40:21.461 --> 00:40:23.623
You left me. didn't you?

623
00:40:25.632 --> 00:40:26.872
Potion. potion!

624
00:40:30.011 --> 00:40:31.291
PHOEBE:
We gotta get out of here.

625
00:40:39.562 --> 00:40:41.223
It's clear!

626
00:40:43.816 --> 00:40:46.148
I'll open the portal.

627
00:40:46.361 --> 00:40:47.817
PHOEBE:
Aah!

628
00:40:48.321 --> 00:40:49.356
Phoebe.

629
00:40:50.198 --> 00:40:51.654
It's Piper.

630
00:40:53.242 --> 00:40:54.653
Her heart is breaking.

631
00:40:55.161 --> 00:40:57.402
-Piper...
-Don't. Stay away from me.

632
00:40:57.580 --> 00:40:59.742
I promise I will explain everything
when we get home.

633
00:40:59.916 --> 00:41:01.247
but right now we need to go.

634
00:41:01.459 --> 00:41:02.540
Home?

635
00:41:02.710 --> 00:41:05.077
We don't have a home. You left us.

636
00:41:06.255 --> 00:41:07.416
Leo. talk to her.

637
00:41:08.716 --> 00:41:09.922
I didn't have a choice.

638
00:41:10.510 --> 00:41:13.798
I became an Elder. It's not something
I wanted. it just happened.

639
00:41:13.972 --> 00:41:15.883
Yeah. see. I know all of this.

640
00:41:16.057 --> 00:41:17.547
Why didn't I remember it?

641
00:41:18.977 --> 00:41:22.561
Because I used my powers
so you wouldn't have to.

642
00:41:24.649 --> 00:41:27.937
Your anger almost destroyed a city.
then your pain almost destroyed you.

643
00:41:28.111 --> 00:41:31.399
I wanted to help you. so you wouldn't
have to deal with it all at once.

644
00:41:32.073 --> 00:41:33.905
So you took my feelings away?

645
00:41:34.075 --> 00:41:35.565
LEO:
No.

646
00:41:35.785 --> 00:41:37.071
Never.

647
00:41:37.245 --> 00:41:40.909
I was gonna reverse the spell slowly so
you could feel a little more every day.

648
00:41:41.124 --> 00:41:45.118
but then somebody did this to me.
Somebody put me here so I couldn't.

649
00:41:48.464 --> 00:41:49.579
I'm sorry.

650
00:41:49.799 --> 00:41:54.418
Look. I don't want to rush you two.
but we have to go.

651
00:41:54.637 --> 00:41:55.798
I have to second that.

652
00:42:08.818 --> 00:42:13.107
You bastard.
how dare you do this to me?

653
00:42:13.281 --> 00:42:15.147
-To our son.
-Phoebe?

654
00:42:15.324 --> 00:42:18.692
We had a life together.
a family. and you destroyed it.

655
00:42:18.870 --> 00:42:20.156
You destroyed me.

656
00:42:20.705 --> 00:42:24.448
You left me alone
to raise our son by myself!

657
00:42:24.625 --> 00:42:26.241
How could you do this?

658
00:42:26.836 --> 00:42:29.043
PHOEBE:
How could you do this?

659
00:42:30.214 --> 00:42:31.295
PHOEBE:
How could you?

660
00:42:52.487 --> 00:42:54.444
I don't feel Piper anymore.

661
00:42:54.655 --> 00:42:56.111
[YELLING]

662
00:42:56.324 --> 00:42:57.359
We have to go.

663
00:43:02.246 --> 00:43:03.782
Come on. Piper. We gotta go.

664
00:43:03.998 --> 00:43:06.706
-Go? Go where?
-Home. hurry!

665
00:43:10.421 --> 00:43:11.661
We gotta leave her. Come on!
